Using ONOS FlowClassifier Driver
================================
To use ONOS FlowClassifier Driver one should
1. Make sure networking-onos code is downloaded and installed.

2. Make sure networking-sfc code is downloaded and installed after below changes done.
   Update onos driver details in setup.cfg (https://github.com/openstack/networking-sfc/blob/master/setup.cfg#L41) with
   onos = networking_onos.services.flowclassifier.OnosFlowClassifierDriver

3. Update "/etc/neutron/neutron.conf" with
   service_plugins = networking_sfc.services.flowclassifier.plugin.FlowClassifierPlugin
   Then stop and start neutron server manually.


Alternative method
===================
If devstack changes supported both repositories, Then follow below steps

1. Update onos driver details in setup.cfg (https://github.com/openstack/networking-sfc/blob/master/setup.cfg#L41) with
   onos = networking_onos.services.flowclassifier.OnosFlowClassifierDriver

2. Update [[local|localrc]] with
   enable_plugin networking-sfc git://git.openstack.org/openstack/networking-sfc
   enable_plugin networking-onos git://git.openstack.org/openstack/networking-onos

3. run ./stack.sh

